The paper deals with the computation of distances and latencies in temporal networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category, as link streams are a model of temporal networks that are commonly used to represent social and information networks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category, as the paper develops different algorithms to efficiently compute distances and latencies in link streams. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category, as the paper deals with the temporal nature of link streams and the computation of shortest fastest paths, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper deals with the analysis and computation of temporal properties of link streams, which can be seen as a system or control problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a less likely category, but still possible, as link streams can be used as input data for machine learning algorithms, and the computation of centrality functions on link streams can be seen as a form of feature engineering.
